[Black "Chapter 1 Classical Formation"]

{In the classical formation after ...Nc6, d6, a6 and Nf6, Black threatens to halt White's momentum with ...Bg4. White can choose between the principled 8. Bf4 and the adventurous, Evans-style 8. b4.}

1. e4 c5 2. d4 cxd4 3. c3 dxc3 4. Nxc3 Nc6 5. Nf3 d6 6. Bc4 {[%entry]} a6 (6... Nf6 7. e5 Ng4! (7... dxe5 8. Qxd8+ Nxd8 (8... Kxd8 9. Ng5 Na5 10. Bb5 Be6 11. Nxe6+ fxe6 12. Be3) 9. Nb5 Rb8 10. Nxe5 e6 11. Bf4) 8. exd6 Qxd6 (8... exd6 9. O-O Be7) 9. O-O e6 10. Nb5 Qb8) 7. O-O Nf6 8. Bf4 (8. b4!? Bg4 9. b5 axb5 (9... Bxf3 10. gxf3 Ne5 11. bxa6) (9... Ne5? 10. Nxe5 dxe5 11. Qb3) 10. Nxb5 e6! 11. Bf4 Be7) (8. h3?! e6) 8... Bg4 (8... e5 9. Ng5!? exf4 10. Nxf7) (8... b5 9. Bxf7+ Kxf7 10. e5) (8... e6 9. Qe2) 9. h3 Bxf3 (9... Bh5 10. g4 Bg6 11. Qe2) 10. Qxf3 e6 11. Rfd1 *

